reviews.text: I thought this was a great restaurant and the food was delicious. They are a little out of the way but the views and food are worth it. Staff were very attentive but not overpowering. Excellent venue for that special occasion. Don’t expect a cheap night though, however the cost is expected for such good quality with a very innovative menu.

My fiancée and I celebrated our 4th anniversary and recent engagement at Alchemy. The ambience was great and we managed to get a table with a view of the story bridge (absolutely stunning at night!). Our waitress, Morgan, made us feel very welcome and was very attentive to us throughout the evening. The food was exceptional! Everything from the presentation to the combination of flavours and textures was beautiful. We want to thank the chef and staff at Alchemy for making our evening such a special one.

Attended as part of a set menu day/business function. Staff presented well and were polite, attentive and helpful. 

Food was adventurous yet basic enough for every tastebud to enjoy. Extensive drinks list to mull over.

And if you were boring and for some reason weren't impressed by the restaurants other great features, the view is always spectacular!
Great quality meals. Great customer service. 11 dollars for still mineral water bottle was a bit much though. My medium rare steak was cooked to perfection. Cocktails were yummy but super small :)

Service from our waitress Lilly was great. French speaking, petite and helpful. The food for me was the disappointment. While the vegetarian menu seemed appealing, my selections from it were underwhelming. The gnocchi were more like pasta shells than any gnocchi I have encountered and not flavoursome either. On the basis of that alone I would have given 3 stars but my colleagues enjoyed their beeftarian dishes so on that basis and the service it gets the 4th star. The location i s good, no doubt. The decor is pleasant.
Love the food here. The best tasting Chinese food I have tasted. The people that work there are so friendly and are always smiling. Keep up the good work !
Outstanding location for delicious chinese food. Visited Sat afternoon. I will be back with my coworkers. Bring your appetite because portions are filling.

This is our go to place for Chinese food.  They even know us by what we order. We think that this place makes some of the best Chinese food for your run of the mill commercial Chinese joints. 
Very pleasant to deal with. Give them a try you will like it.
Quick, consistent, excellent service with a smile. Love them.
Absolutely wonderful food. Quick and fresh. Nothing was reheated or cold. Great portions.

Havana belongs on any foodie's "Note to Self" page during visits to Bar Harbor.  Innovative menu for vegans and meat-lovers alike (rare!) and an inviting wine list to boot.  That they remain open most of the year - even off season - adds to our delight in visiting.  Love this place.
Really lovely little restaurant with a friendly staff.  The food was very good and the beer selection decent.  Although they got both of my beer orders wrong I would definitely go back.

Excellent restaurant. Had the fish of the day and by far was the best fish I've ever had. Portion is a little small and wait times can be long, but it is what it is. A few other patrons had the tapas and they looked excellent as well. Would recommend.

Our experience at Havana is second to none. The service was incredible matched only by the food and drinks. Enrique our server was fantastic. I highly recommend the black bean soup, the empanadas and the farmhouse salad, and the Havana martini is tasty.  Thanks!!

Best paella I've ever eaten - generous helping of perfectly-cooked seafood and the saucy rice was just spot on. But everything we had was delicious anyway. The mashed potatoes with coconut that came with one of the daily specials was just... So good...

The wine list is nuts, apparently one of the largest in the region. They have the little notes in the wine menu to help you choose, and we were really happy with the bottle we had.

And of course, the service was excellent. They open at 5pm but it appears that the live music starts a little later.

DO NOT ORDER FROM THIS PLACE THEY WILL SCAM YOU! 
Ordered a burrito and burrito bowl off of GOJEK delivery from here and the resturant literally doubled the price on us. The driver gave us the receipt. 

The burrito bowl was super tiny and the burrito was soggy and flavorless. Save yourself the trouble

Great restaurant! 
Extremely fresh food and staff is really cool!
One of my favorites in Bali!
Setting was a bit rural but they had very good food for a good price. Both of us ordered chicken quesadilla :)

It was terrible. The carne (beef) nachos was basically a tasteless bit of diced stesk on top of deep fried oily corn chips topped with salad and a bit of avocado and beans. All the ingredients were correct but there was no taste and no love. Staff were good and the prices were low but deservedly so. Definately won't go back. My husband had the tacos which were exactly the same but in a different shell. We both left 90% of our meal on our plates. One positive was the beer was really cold.

Ordered via delivery. Price was literally double what was stated via go food and driver had no invoice. I can understand small differences but this was a joke. Burrito was terrible with no guac or sour cream, 90% rice. Tried calling the number to query the price difference but it's not in service. Avoid this scam restaurant and get great burritos at taco beach or lacalaca.

Delicious and healthy lunch. I loved it, full of veges and chicken in a rich curry, coconut milk sauce. Fabulous cinnamon iced tea. Gracious and friendly service. Fun atmosphere. Will be back again and again!

In a city with abundant good eating places, the Rainbow remains our hands down first choice year after year. Delicious choices for both vegetarians and meat eaters. Breakfast and lunch only and both menus sport excellent choices. Great friendly service, warm cozy brick building with charming interior (formerly a bank with the vault still visible).One of the best if not THE best patio in town. Love love love it.

I was told this was a  vegetarian spot, so wasn't stoked at first. Then I found out they are more than willing to add bacon to anything. Everything I had was incredible! I tried everyone else's food, and my Benedict was incredible! Their pumpkin something pancakes were to die for and made great French toast sticks the next morning. Can't wait to try more of their food!

I’ve loved this place for a long time and have been many many times. Recently however, I’ve taken a break since there is a lot of inconsistency with their food quality and playing, though service is almost always great! This is the reason for 4 stars instead of 5. 

I really want this to be my favorite breakfast restaurant in Fort Collins, perhaps if they can improve consistency this will happen. Either way, I highly recommend you give it a try if you haven’t!

This locally owned restaurant is what Fort Collins is all about! Amazing food. Great people. Excellent service. The outside patio is gorgeous-surrounded by trees and little vegetable gardens. I love it!

I always go there for their chocolate pastries..... best they have is choco fantasy.... enjoy it hot with scoop of vanilla ice-cream..... must try when you visit there.... other things are also good there.... like their sandwiches and coffes and other cold beverages........
I love this place... Visiting this since 2012... Yes.. best things do happen over a cup of coffee...  Lots of memories for lifetime...
A nice place if you want to spend time leisurely. ( without spending too much) Ps: We ordered only a tea and coffee so no comments about the food. Service was fine.

Awesome beverage as well as food of CCD. 
Well coordinated staff ...................
Nice place to enjoy coffee. Good Environment
Central Plaza Chiang Rai is the best shopping mall in the city and the entire province. The food court on the lowest floor also has very good Northern Thai food.

I came here looking for the AIS telephone shop. Found it very quickly the people were super nice and got my business done in a timely fashion. It's a very comfortable Mall only two floors so it's not packed with stuff.

It's a mall, which you could expect to find everything; food, cloth, grocery, gadget, cinema etc. Ranging from the cheap to the affordable brand name ones, Central Plaza Chiang Rai is the solution for whom looking for the all-in-one shopping place. There are also various kinds of taxi service. But beware! the price can be bargain.

Great little mall with movie theater. They offer a free shuttle to and from town as it is a 15 drive out of the city core. If you decide to drive parking is free but can be a bit of an issue. It is often full.

Biggest mall in Chiang Rai.  Similar to most Central Plazas around the country, but perhaps smaller. Great place to shop and find big city items. Top store had a great choice of imported foods, better than in most cites in Thailand. As with any Thai mall, parking is a challenge on weekends.
Food was decent and the prices were very reasonable. There's plenty of choices from one end of the street to the next end. A must visit when you come to Chumphon.
So fun ! Got the deepfried bread with coconut frosting
Night market not big but definetelly worth visiting
Small nigh street shopping.
Nice attraction for tourist that visit Chumphon. The mango rice and the thai pastry shop next to it is a must try and you can find all sorts of delicious desserts along the night bazaar.
Always a pleasure to spend time at Braverly.  It's a blessing to be able to support young people in making their lives better.  Delicious food and one of the best drip coffees in MaeSot
Biggest cup of coffee on town. Always improving thier service.
Me and my kids love coming to Braverly for smoothie bowls and bagels. They've got great food.
Great atmosphere and service!
This is a fine typical Bolognese restaurant. So authentic food and very good. Monday's it is closed

Great service,  but highly over priced at 97€. 
We had 2 starters, 2 meat dishes, 1 plate of fruit, 1 large beer and an espresso. My main at 18€ of thinly sliced cold roast beef with nothing on the side, didn’t warrant the price. I left hungry and highly disappointed. 
The restaurant also had damp smell to it.

I was there some 8 years ago and loved the traditional food. The service even then was a little abrupt and that hasn't changed (despite me trying hard with my basic Italian). We were there for a short lunch, It's ok but you can find a friendlier experience of traditional food else where especially for the prices. Our lasagne was exceptional, but sadly I don't think I'd recommend Diana over some other places we've been recommended over the last week.
Tipical ,old traditional Italian restaurant! Very good.
A very good restaurant in Bologna, the services are good and waiters are very nice.

Best place to visit . It is found inside Addis Ababa university , College of natural and computational science compound .
Several wild animals are found reserved ( killed and dried ) 
It has entrance fee 
For regular students (AAU students ) and children - 5 birr
For adult Ethiopians - 15 birr
For foreigners - 100 birr 
If you want to record and take a picture you have to pay another fee .
But all the payments are totally worth it .
I RECOMMEND YOU TO VISIT THIS PLACE .
Museum was closed despite that it's supposed to be opened.  No explanations.  Don't bother going.
It is consist of historical and inspire objects.
Easy to miss. Still worth a walk through for the insect and mammal collections, modest though they are. Gives a sense of the biological  diversity of the country.

There's something for everyone at City Cafe! I love the variety of appetizers and entrees, as well as their selection of beverages. There are areas of the restaurant that are quite chatty, as well as quiet if you're looking for a more intimate conversation. I've never had anything short of excellent customer service. I highly recommend the sangria and Morrocan burger! Very filling and healthy and not greasy at all.

Just awesome!  We had brunch there this morning. Andrew was our server and he was so nice. The angry omelet was very good. And the ambiance was fun, too. The only thing needing improvement was the coffee. Very bitter. Not sure if it was the coffee or the brewing, but something was off.

Went to brunch today with my wife for my birthday.  We have been going to city cafe for years and it’s always been a favorite.  Today was an awful experience.  Our appetizer never came (which we were most looking forward to), and my wife’s food was not only incorrect, but stone cold when it arrived.  My omelet was horribly over cooked.  We usually don’t say anything but today we did, and we got a ‘sorry about that’ from our waiter and that was it.  A $75 bill for inedible food was delivered with no offer of a replacement meal or the appetizer.  Have to say that will unfortunately be our last visit to this place.  We ended up at the owl bar eating pizza...which was fantastic.  Should have went there in the first place.

They forgot to microwave the crab cake enough (ice cold in center, seriously, others felt it and were disgusted) then they brought a "replacement" out on a dirty plate after we all finished our meals. . . 
. . . Regardless, it's a dying neighborhood and they don't care about cutting corners.  Just look at the feedback!  They won't even take a couple minutes to address issues or say thanks.  Just walk another block or two and have an enjoyable meal.

Nice laid back atmosphere. The food is very good and tasty. Service was fast and I did get every one of my requests for my food exactly right as requested.  Extra sauce for my  brussel sprouts and the blackened salmon was crisp  on the outside and tender on the inside. My my my!

The botanic gardens are beautiful! Very well kept. I enjoyed the greenhouses too, such a variety of lovely plants. I can tell a lot of care goes in to looking after them. I wish there were some animals in the tropical house. Nice for an afternoon stroll.

Really blissful ..you can have a good walk here.
of course when the weather is good.. 
You can see a wide variety of flowers.. well maintained.

The Ulster museum at one corner for the park is definitely worth a visit...& there is no entry fee.
Wonderful gardens, and amazing hot houses. Beautifully set out.  And with the Ulster Museum on the grounds. Amazing.  All lovers of plant life, and Creation in general will enjoy time spent here.

Had a great day walking around the craft fair. Seen many spectacular flowers, massive vegetables and lots of stalls selling home made produces. The fudge was fantastic.

Found the Belfast ukelele jam group playing in a marquee. Wow great music.

Pleasant in the early Spring. The flowerbeds are full of vibrant colour. The hothouses are rich with blooms and scents. The lawns have not yet shaken off their winter rough and are damp, but not for long. The renovated tropical ravine is superb and the museum is nearby if it rains or you need a snack. If it's sunny, go and look at the herbacious borders; sit and listen to the bees at work.
Very nice spot, with sea view when you come out, very nice
Beautiful cathedral ! We've had a good office with a welcoming priest
Hardly a cathedral. Dont go there
Nothing very special
Cool Place
Show!

É claro que não seria algo grandioso pois o Governador Valadares é uma cidade pequena. Ademais, havia uma área não completa que parecia ser meio abandonada. No entanto, o conteúdo apresentado neste museu é muito informador sobre a cidade, verdadeiramente aprendi muito sobre a cidade do meu pai e senti mais orgulho da história da minha família. Além do mais, a arquitetura antiga preservada agrada os olhos. O atendimento também foi ótimo, as moças que trabalham lá conversavam conosco e nos ofereciam mais informações sobre o museu e a cidade. É uma pena que muitos não conhecem este museu, pois realmente vale a pena o visitar para conhecer cada vez mais a nossa história!
Uma excelente opção para conhecer a história de Governador Valadares. O acervo poderia melhorar. A planta original da cidade precisa de restauração urgente.
Me surpreendeu. Apesar do espaço ser alugado, tem muitos atrativos e retrata a história da cidade. Mais pessoas deveriam conhecer.
Relembrei de coisas que fizeram parte da minha família e da minha vida.

Fascinating medieval buildings and unique history...

However,  for  the €13 (plus €5 for audio guide), would have expected to see and learn WAY more.   Of two sections,  we saw 7 rooms, some yards and some little exhibits - done in an easy 40 minutes. 

The LOUVRE cost €20 including 'skip the line'.   Enjoy the great character and charm of Mantova , taste the food and breads, then go to the Louvre instead.

We were amazed at the stunning paintings, fabrics and sculpture. This is a remarkable place to visit. One suggestion: the palace is so large and there is so much to see that it is worth splitting up the visit and perhaps taking a cafe or restaurant break half way through. This is perfectly possible as there are different buildings with separate entrances so visitors can come and go freely.
Gorgeous renaissance palace, worth a visit. The line can get quite long on weekends.
Vast place. did not have enough time in schedule to fully explore.  Nice town
Beautiful monument full of history in Mantova Italy

If you are looking for somewhere inexpensive to have some lunch then come here as you have plenty to choose from. At this centre you cam buy almost anything from pork to chicken and everything in between and it will just cost under S$10 For a nice meal.
We have pork and duck meat with a pork soup and it was delicious. If you want to try something different then go for the black skin chicken. For drinks you can get anything from water to tea or coffee.
I had so much fun that hippies are so cool I smoke some of the best weed for the best price

A great space and part of Berkeley's story, student accommodation not sure? A refuge and a place of reflection for Berkeley siders, keep People's Park as it is, a moving story and inportant history that should be preserved and improved.

Peoples Park is a precious green space. I play live acoustic music at Peoples Park whenever I get a chance, guitar songs, jazz, funk, folk, rock, samba, bossa nova, percussion... I have old friends there and did community gardening there for five years, growing 13 foot tall corn and green beans, and all kinds of stuff. The trees and plants there are good old friends too. I've heard lots of great bands on the Free Speech Stage, summer concerts, the Berkeley World Music series, drum jams, dancing. Its very interesting, I've learned a lot there, talking to people, about history, people, culture, plants, gardening.

I have always loved this old park.
Sad it is always under attack and it is purposely kept decrepit by the University to justify building on it.
Guess everyone will use Williard Park should the unelected have their way.
Best dumplings I’ve ever had anywhere! And the owner is always so happy and friendly to everyone.. What a find!

A great choice for something quick and healthy in central!
 
I love coming here for quick breakfasts and lunches. Not only are the dumplings delicious, but they are healthy as well! A lot of times when you think of “healthy food” it’s often something cold. But dumplings are a great warm alternative!

Moreover, this place offers a lot of dumplings options that are rare to find elsewhere. The menu differs everyday of the week so it’s fun to try something different from time to time

When I come here for breakfasts, I can see the ladies here wrapping the dumplings themselves, giving this place a warm and homey vibe (moreover you can tell that the dumplings are all made in-house)!

This is my go-to for quick breakfasts and lunches and everyone that I’ve brought here loves this place too!
Fried dumpling is like Korean style. We call it twi-gim-man-du
Nice dumplings with reasonable price.
Diculous home made dumplings

There is a large stone covered area, like a large town square at the Town Hall. There are sidewalk cafes, many kinds of shops, and an information/visitors office where you can look for maps, tours, info, etc. At opposite end of square from Town Hall is a beautiful large cathedral.  Mozart and Handel played the large pipe organ there back in the day.
Beautiful building and area.
Historic City
Very nice place, have been inside and its just as nice there as from the outside
No need to watch your wallet here
